design:
Expose one advanced external Helix object instead of mode/backend choices. Proposed JSONC shape:

"helix": {
  "external": null
}

or:

"helix": {
  "external": {
    "binary": "/path/to/hx",
    "runtime_path": "/path/to/helix/runtime"
  }
}

Both fields are required together. Do not accept a binary without runtime_path, because Yazelix has already had user-facing Helix runtime mismatch and package-collision issues. Do not accept shell snippets with args; users who need flags should provide a wrapper executable and a matching runtime_path.

Default null means the bundled Yazelix Helix Steel fork and its matching runtime. External means user-owned binary/runtime at the user's risk, launched under the Yazelix Helix config contract.
